head: 5. Georeferencing
inf1: Magick is going to happen (or not).
inf2: You need to have a file with GCP points in /data/templates/geopoints/ with the ending .points. The expected format is the default export of GCPs from QGIS containing the columns mapX, mapY, pixelX, and pixelY. This should be the first line the .points file. In case if you have any other information, you can manually remove it for now.You can find the output at the data/output/georeferencing/ folder.
input: For which site listing the maps
